  "decision": {
    "promote": false,
    "read": "The selective multi-warp MORI compact copy patch is correct under both low-row and high-row parity, but it does not materialize into an e2e throughput uplift. The six-step 8xMI350 gate regresses about 4.2% versus the previous native count-aware branch over steps 2-6 and about 6.4% over steps 4-6. The step-2 profile shows dispatch launch improved relative to older source-scatter profiles, but combine launch and the unchanged helper/normal-EP graph still dominate. Do not continue copy-schedule knob work as the main line; move to final expert-major/compact-return ABI collapse and an explicitly pinned no-MTP/no-mHC Goal-1 native-vs-standard A/B."
